data.content:
**In .NET 11, sync I/O on the Cosmos DB provider is fully removed — no opt-in exists.** Your `ToList()`, `First()`, `Count()`, and `SaveChanges()` calls will **always throw** at runtime, regardless of configuration.

### What to do

Convert your repository to async:

```csharp
public class ProductRepository
{
    private readonly CosmosDbContext _context;

    public async Task<List<Product>> GetAllAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.ToListAsync();
    }

    public async Task<Product> GetByIdAsync(int id)
    {
        return await _context.Products.FirstAsync(p => p.Id == id);
    }

    public async Task<int> GetCountAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.CountAsync();
    }

    public async Task SaveAsync(Product product)
    {
        _context.Products.Add(product);
        await _context.SaveChangesAsync();
    }
}
```

This will ripple up to callers — they must also become `async`/`await`. There is no workaround; the Cosmos SDK is async-only and EF Core 11 no longer wraps it.

Also watch for the **owned collections** change: empty owned collections now return an empty list instead of `null`, so update any `is null` checks to `.Count == 0`.
